Interface ClaimContactRoleOwner

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Bean, com.guidewire.pl.persistence.core.BeanMethods, BundleProvider, ClaimContactRoleOwner, java.lang.Comparable<Bean>, Editable, com.guidewire.cc.domain.contact.EntityContactRoleOwner, com.guidewire.commons.entity.Keyable, KeyableBean, com.guidewire.commons.entity.Sourceable, Versionable

    @Generated(value="com.guidewire.pl.metadata.codegen.Codegen",
           comments="ClaimContactRoleOwner.eti;ClaimContactRoleOwner.eix;ClaimContactRoleOwner.etx")
public interface ClaimContactRoleOwner
extends Editable, ClaimContactRoleOwner
    ClaimContactRoleOwner Interface for entities that can "own" ClaimContactRoles. Marking an entity as a ClaimContactRoleOwner means that it can be associated with ContactRoles. In practical terms, this means the entity will get ContactRole-based accessors that can then be used as items in NVVs. This gives a customers a way to add arbitrary Contacts to an entity, and have those roles appear in Parties Involved.
